OL,3,CBrighton manager Roberto De Zerbi to
OL,4,Cleave the club by 'mutual agreement'
OL,6,FIn a statement De Zerbi paid tribute
OL,7,Fto the squad. He said, "I am very sad
OL,8,Fto be leaving Brighton, but I am very
OL,9,Fproud of what my players and staff
OL,10,Fhave achieved with the support of
OL,11,Feveryone at the club and our amazing
OL,12,Ffans in the past two historical
OL,13,Fseasons.
OL,15,F"We have agreed to end my time at
OL,16,FBrighton so that the club and I can
OL,17,Fcontinue to work in the way that suits
OL,18,Feach of us best, following our own
OL,19,Fideas and visions, as well as our work
OL,20,Fand human values.
