OL,3,CBrighton manager Roberto De Zerbi to
OL,4,Cleave the club by 'mutual agreement'
OL,6,F"I have really enjoyed an intense and
OL,7,Fchallenging two years working in the
OL,8,FPremier League, not least competing in
OL,9,Ffour major competitions this season.
OL,10,FLeaving now provides me with time to
OL,11,Ftake a break before deciding on my
OL,12,Ffuture plans."
OL,14,FChairman, Tony Bloom, said, "Roberto
OL,15,Fhas given us two excellent seasons of
OL,16,Fservice in which he has led the club
OL,17,Fto new heights, not least our first
OL,18,Fever European campaign which will live
OL,19,Flong in the memory of Albion fans."
